RULE c_soft | c before e, i, or y | c becomes /s/
RULE c_hard | c before a, o, u, or consonant | c becomes /k/

RULE g_soft | g before e, i, or y (SOMETIMES) | g becomes /dʒ/
RULE g_hard | g before a, o, u, or consonant (ALWAYS) | g stays /g/

RULE qu | q is always followed by u | qu together sound /kw/

RULE double_consonant | when a consonant is doubled | it makes one sound, the vowel before it stays short




