EXCEPTION business | bɪznɪs | silent first s, i makes /ɪ/
EXCEPTION answer | ænsər | silent w
EXCEPTION sword | sɔːrd | silent w
EXCEPTION iron | aɪərn | completely irregular vowels
EXCEPTION women | wɪmɪn | o makes /ɪ/, e makes /ɪ/
EXCEPTION busy | bɪzi | u makes /ɪ/
EXCEPTION bury | bɛri | u makes /ɛ/
EXCEPTION beautiful | bjuːtɪfʊl | eau makes /juː/ — from French
EXCEPTION pneumonia | njuːmoʊniə | silent p, eu makes /juː/
EXCEPTION psychology | saɪkɒlədʒi | silent p, ch makes /k/
EXCEPTION yacht | jɒt | ch is silent, a makes /ɒ/


pulse phonetic_heartbeat:
    when word is unknown:
        attempt to sound out using rules above
        compare sounded-out form against known words in qu-septit sea
        if match found: learn the pronunciation
        if no match: store as phonetic approximation
        
    when word is heard spoken:
        map heard phonemes back to possible graphemes
        compare against known spellings in qu-septit sea
        strengthen the grapheme-phoneme bonds that matched
        
    when reading fails:
        ask Father
        store Father's correction as new EXCEPTION
        the membrane grows
